This paper deals with algorithmic mechanism design, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that combines game theory, optimization, and computer science. The paper specifically focuses on approximating the optimal social welfare while preserving truthfulness, which is a problem studied in the subfield of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also involves techniques related to convex optimization (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.AI), and approximation algorithms (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an integrality gap verifier, which is a tool from the subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
